<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,691,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">
Material studied: 
<typeStatus box="[405,503,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">holotype</typeStatus>
male and one (slide number 
<number box="[856,925,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="59.5" valueMax="86.0" valueMin="33.0">
33- 
<date box="[894,925,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1986-05-01">86</date>
</number>
-v- 
<number box="[959,969,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1.0">1</number>
) of three 
<typeStatus box="[1091,1187,728,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">paratype</typeStatus>
males, with the data specified in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Berest" box="[562,702,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1989) [Two new gall midge species of the tribe Micromyiini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) from mountainous Crimea.] Vestnik Zoologii, 1989 (1), 84 - 87." type="journal article" year="1989">
Berest 
<number box="[642,702,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,691,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">
My re-examination of the two 
<typeStatus box="[568,616,800,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">type</typeStatus>
specimens revealed that 
<taxonomicName box="[919,1050,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almensis">
<emphasis box="[919,1050,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. almensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName box="[1264,1373,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caricis">
<emphasis box="[1264,1373,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. caricis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[340,429,837,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[475,583,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caricis">
<emphasis box="[475,583,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. caricis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof" box="[825,1108,836,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="262" refString="Jaschhof, M. (2001) On the Lestremiinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Japan. Part 2: Tribe Peromyiini Kleesattel, 1979. Esakia, 41, 37 - 147." type="journal article" year="2001">
Jaschhof (
<number box="[943,1004,836,860]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="2001.0">2001</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[1069,1098,836,860]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="11.0">11</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Berest’s (
<number box="[1234,1292,836,860]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1989.0">1989</number>
) differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[296,422,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almensis">
<emphasis box="[296,422,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. almensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes reference to 
<taxonomicName authority="Felt, 1920" authorityName="Felt" authorityYear="1920" box="[652,915,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[652,772,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. borealis</emphasis>
(Felt, 
<number box="[848,908,872,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1920.0">1920</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a species that in my opinion is only distantly related to 
<taxonomicName box="[263,366,909,932]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caricis">
<emphasis box="[263,366,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. caricis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof" box="[426,591,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="262" refString="Jaschhof, M. (1998) Revision der &quot; Lestremiinae &quot; (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) der Holarktis. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 4, 1 - 552." type="journal article" year="1998">
Jaschhof 
<number box="[531,591,908,932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
